<li><a href="#org720e263">79.5. Question: What are the benefits of stabilizing?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#orge17a108">79.5.1. Answer: The benefits of stabilizing include:</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#orgacdc39c">79.6. Question: What is Rule 10b-18?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#org13c831c">79.6.1. Answer: Rule 10b-18 is a Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) rule that provides a safe harbor for repurchases of a company's own stock. The rule allows companies to repurchase their stock without being accused of market manipulation, as long as they follow certain procedures.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#org8f53aab">79.7. Question: What are the requirements of Rule 10b-18?</a>
