<ul>
<li><a href="#orgd8e5274">79.9.1. Answer: The penalties for violating Rule 10b-18 can be severe. Companies that violate the rule can be fined up to \$10 million, and individuals can be fined up to \$5 million and imprisoned for up to 20 years.</a></li>
