<li><a href="#orgc603805">80. Questions regarding the 40-day average weighted price and the 10% repurchase limit, followed by the answers:</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#org1c00a34">80.1. Question: What is the purpose of the 40-day average weighted price requirement?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#org0683c07">80.1.1. Answer: The purpose of the 40-day average weighted price requirement is to prevent companies from artificially inflating the price of their own shares by repurchasing them at prices that are above the market price.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#orge3bbb7a">80.2. Question: How is the 40-day average weighted price calculated?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#orgb64fd9f">80.2.1. Answer: The 40-day average weighted price is calculated by taking the sum of the product of the price of a security and the number of shares traded at that price during the preceding 40 trading days, and then dividing by the total number of shares traded during the 40-day period.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#orge0291a8">80.3. Question: What are the exceptions to the 40-day average weighted price requirement?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#org99fcad7">80.3.1. Answer: There are a few exceptions to the 40-day average weighted price requirement. These exceptions include:</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#org659ecf6">80.4. Question: What is the 10% repurchase limit?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#orgdc21d00">80.4.1. Answer: The 10% repurchase limit is a rule that limits the amount of a company's outstanding shares that it can repurchase in a 12-month period. The limit is 10% of the company's outstanding shares as of the beginning of the repurchase period.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#org62274c1">80.5. Question: What are the consequences of violating the 10% repurchase limit?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#orgb86be8d">80.5.1. Answer: The consequences of violating the 10% repurchase limit can vary depending on the specific circumstances. However, in general, violating the limit can result in civil penalties being imposed on the company.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#org1390755">80.6. Question: What are the different ways that a company can repurchase its own shares?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#org00705f8">80.6.1. Answer: There are a few different ways that a company can repurchase its own shares. These methods include:</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#orgc12ad31">80.7. Question: What are the benefits of a company repurchasing its own shares?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#orgce03379">80.7.1. Answer: There are a few benefits to a company repurchasing its own shares. These benefits include:</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#org1fe8734">80.8. Question: What are the risks of a company repurchasing its own shares?</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#org239e31d">80.8.1. Answer: There are a few risks to a company repurchasing its own shares. These risks include:</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
