<div id="outline-container-org90c1cdc" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org90c1cdc"><span class="section-number-2">76.</span> Possible questions regarding Rule 10b-5, followed by the answer:</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-76">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orga04d9f4" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orga04d9f4"><span class="section-number-3">76.1.</span> Question: What is Rule 10b-5?</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-76-1">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgd56f3c5" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgd56f3c5"><span class="section-number-4">76.1.1.</span> Answer: Rule 10b-5 is a rule of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 that prohibits the use of manipulative and deceptive devices in the trading of securities. It is one of the most important anti-fraud provisions in the securities laws.</h4>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org4101ee1" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org4101ee1"><span class="section-number-3">76.2.</span> Question: What is material non-public information?</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-76-2">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgab1bb63" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgab1bb63"><span class="section-number-4">76.2.1.</span> Answer: Material non-public information is information that could significantly affect the price of a security if it were known to the public. This could include information about the company's financial performance, mergers and acquisitions, or product development.</h4>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org456787a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org456787a"><span class="section-number-3">76.3.</span> Question: What is insider trading?</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-76-3">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgf434743" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgf434743"><span class="section-number-4">76.3.1.</span> Answer: Insider trading is the buying or selling of a security based on material non-public information. It is a form of securities fraud that can have serious consequences for the individuals involved.</h4>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org2bb7725" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org2bb7725"><span class="section-number-3">76.4.</span> Question: What are the penalties for insider trading?</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-76-4">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org60bc2b0" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org60bc2b0"><span class="section-number-4">76.4.1.</span> Answer: The penalties for insider trading can be severe. Individuals who are convicted of insider trading can be fined up to $5 million and/or imprisoned for up to 20 years.</h4>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org1c390a1" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org1c390a1"><span class="section-number-3">76.5.</span> Question: How can I avoid insider trading?</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-76-5">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org930e2ac" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org930e2ac"><span class="section-number-4">76.5.1.</span> Answer: There are a number of things you can do to avoid insider trading. First, you should be aware of the rules governing insider trading. Second, you should avoid trading in securities if you have any material non-public information about the company. Third, you should be careful about what you say to others about material non-public information.</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-76-5-1">
<p>
I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.
